name: Jimbarwana Hotel
address: Jl. Udayana No.2, Baler Bale Agung, Kec. Negara, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali 82212, Indonesia
review 1:
OK for the price.
TV is connected to the internet too.
review 2: Nice restaurant with delicious food at cheap prices. They offer local & Western food choices.  The staff was friendly & helpful. They have a nice pool that offers day use only right now. The villas & hotel are having the finishings touches added before opening to the public.
review 3: We stayed in the apartments next to the swimming pool. Large rooms but very tired decor. Internet ok. The restaurant serves good food but the service is very slow.
review 4: A semi modern building welcomes you, mediocre lobby receives you, but old rooms is where you'll sleep in. The room got patches on the wall and floor. No phones on 3rd floor. Bed is clean, though. Bathroom isn't fancy but you can take proper shower there. Food isn't so expensive, but the restaurant isn't for 24 hours. Hospitable staffs, very helpful. The clean bed, well-priced food, and hospitable staffs are what gets this hotel 3 stars from me.
review 5: Reasonable hotel for Nagara, rooms old but clean, restaurant attached you can get coffee average food
